RTMES on M3 subsystem of OMAP4 SoC

This BSP is developed for running RTEMS on OMAP4's M3 cores.
RTEMS is loaded by Linux via remoteproc framework. 

For running this BSP, you need
*)OMAP4 SoC, such as Pandaboard.
*)Linux supported remoteproc for OMAP4. upstream_rpmsg branch 
from git://github.com/GAnthony/upstream-rpmsg.git
*)Linux modules to load/unload RTEMS. 
An example is at c/src/lib/libbsp/arm/omap4m3/module/rproc.c

Instructions to run RTEMS.
*)Copy program.exe to /lib/firmware/ducati-m3-core0.xem3.
*)Load rproc.ko module to load /lib/firmware/ducati-m3-core0.xem3
*)You can see the output form /sys/kernel/debug/remoteproc/omap-rproc.1/trace0